The objective of the game is to get a ha: The objective of the game is to get a hand total of closer to 21 than the dealer without going over 21.
The numeral cards 2 to 10 have their fac: The numeral cards 2 to 10 have their face values, Jacks, Queens and Kings are valued at 10, and Aces can have a value of either 1 or 11.
The Ace is always valued at 11 unless t: The Ace is always valued at 11 unless that would result in the hand going over 21, in which case it is valued as 1.
After you place a bet the dealer then de: After you place a bet the dealer then deals you two cards face up.
The dealer also gets two cards - one fac: The dealer also gets two cards - one face up and another face down.
You have several choices to continue the: You have several choices to continue the game.
If your first two cards are acceptable,: If your first two cards are acceptable, you can stand.
If you would like more cards to improve: If you would like more cards to improve your hand total, the dealer will deal you more cards, one at a time, until you either bust (go over 21) or you choose to stand.
If you have a hand total that is advanta: If you have a hand total that is advantageous to you but you need to take an additional card you can double your initial wager and the dealer will deal you only 1 additional card.
If you are dealt a pair (2 cards of equa: If you are dealt a pair (2 cards of equal value) you have the option to put out a second wager and the dealer will split the two cards so that each card will become the first card on two new hands.
You will be dealt a second card on each: You will be dealt a second card on each hand and can play each hand one after another.
Insurance is a side bet offered when the: Insurance is a side bet offered when the dealer has an Ace as an up-card.
You can put up a wager equal to half you: You can put up a wager equal to half your original bet, which will get paid 2 to 1 if the dealer has a Blackjack.
If your hand has not busted, then it is: If your hand has not busted, then it is time for the dealer to play their hand.
The dealer will first flip over their \": The dealer will first flip over their "hole card" (the face down card) and add up their 2-card hand.
If the dealer has a hand total of 17 or: If the dealer has a hand total of 17 or higher, they will automatically stand.
If the dealer has a hand total of 16 or: If the dealer has a hand total of 16 or lower, they will take additional cards until they either bust or get a hand total of 17 or higher.
Insurance costs half bet and pays 2:1: Insurance costs half bet and pays 2:1
The objective of the game is to collect: The objective of the game is to collect one of the possible winning combinations based on the 5-card draw.
Choose your bet and one of the 5 payout: Choose your bet and one of the 5 payout columns.
Each payout column corresponds to a numb: Each payout column corresponds to a number of coins from 1 to 5 (left to right).
Your bet is additionally multiplied by t: Your bet is additionally multiplied by the selected number of coins.
So if you bet 5 credits and choose the m: So if you bet 5 credits and choose the most right payout column you will be charged total 25 credits for playing a game.
In the first round you receive 5 random: In the first round you receive 5 random cards.
You can then exchange any one of the rec: You can then exchange any one of the received cards for another (or all of them) in order to collect a winning combination.
To keep a specific card click on it and: To keep a specific card click on it and it will be hels during the second draw.
